ROOT CAUSE: Claude CLI uses newline-delimited JSON for MCP stdio, NOT Content-Length headers. mcp_tasks.py used json+newline (worked). All other servers used Content-Length protocol (hung forever). The MCP spec says Content-Length but the Claude CLI doesn't implement it — it reads one JSON object per line. Fix: all servers now use sys.stdout.write(json.dumps(obj) + newline). Also: host-side MCP servers spawn in background to avoid blocking server startup, and container-path servers are filtered out.
